<chapter xml:id="ch-color-science" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Color Science</title>

  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          Students will be able to explain the basics of color space and color gamuts.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Students will be able to describe the relationship between the Kelvin temperature scale and the Kelvin color scale.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Students will be able to describe additive and subtractive colors.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Students will be able to describe the theory of mixing colors in the context of both RGB and CMYK.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <introduction>
    <p> Color is a physical phenomenon, psychological phenomenon, and a biological phenomenon. </p>
  </introduction>

